# ABA Note Companion

## Ownership

- Frontend: collects session facts and one replacement-program/percentage assignment per hour.
- Backend: validates those hourly assignments, loads the client profile/assessment, calls the model,
  and assembles the locked opening/final section.
- Model: writes one natural ABC paragraph per hour and chooses activity, behavior, and intervention
  details from the supplied client context.

## Non-negotiable data flow

- Never generate without the client's on-file assessment when the product requires one.
- Never replace, reorder, rotate, or auto-fill an hourly program selected in the app.
- Never recalculate or substitute the app-selected percentage; reproduce it exactly.
- The same program may be assigned to multiple hours.
- `sessionHours` equals the required number of ABC paragraphs.

## What is intentionally not a backend rule

There are no backend rules for behavior-function pairing, intervention count/order, safety chains,
topography wording, subjective-word lists, acquisition-only framing, reinforcer wording inside the
clinical body, or sentence-by-sentence ABC templates.

The locked shell remains in `aba-note-locked-prose.mdc`.
